    content.flex.flex-col.items-center.justify-center
      hero.flex.w-full.max-w-6xl.flex-row.items-center.justify-between.p-8(class='md:my-16')
        .flex.w-full.flex-col.space-y-8
          .flex.w-full.flex-col.space-y-4
            h1.select-none.font-poppins.text-5xl.font-bold.text-neutral-900 Code of Conduct
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900 Last Updated 11th Febuary 2024
          .flex.w-full.flex-col.space-y-4
            h2.select-none.font-poppins.text-3xl.font-bold.text-neutral-900 Our Pledge
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900
              | We as members, contributors, and leaders pledge to make participation in our community a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, body size, visible or invisible disability, ethnicity, sex characteristics, gender identity and expression, level of experience, education, socio-economic status, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.
              br
              br
              | We pledge to act and interact in ways that contribute to an open, welcoming, diverse, inclusive, and healthy community.
            h2.select-none.font-poppins.text-3xl.font-bold.text-neutral-900 Our Standards
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900
              | Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment for our community include: Demonstrating empathy and kindness toward other people, being respectful of differing opinions, viewpoints, and experiences, giving and gracefully accepting constructive feedback, accepting responsibility and apologizing to those affected by our mistakes and learning from the experience, and focusing on what is best not just for us as individuals, but for the overall community
              br
              br
              | Examples of unacceptable behavior include: The use of sexualized language or imagery, and sexual attention or advances of any kind, trolling, insulting or derogatory comments, and personal or political attacks, public or private harassment, publishing others' private information, such as a physical or email address, without their explicit permission, and other conduct which could reasonably be considered inappropriate in a professional setting
            h2.select-none.font-poppins.text-3xl.font-bold.text-neutral-900 Enforcement Responsibilities
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900
              | Community leaders are responsible for clarifying and enforcing our standards of acceptable behavior and will take appropriate and fair corrective action in response to any behavior that they deem inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful.
              br
              br
              | Community leaders have the right and responsibility to remove, edit, or reject comments, commits, code, wiki edits, issues, and other contributions that are not aligned to this Code of Conduct, and will communicate reasons for moderation decisions when appropriate.
            h2.select-none.font-poppins.text-3xl.font-bold.text-neutral-900 Scope
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900 This Code of Conduct applies within all community spaces, and also applies when an individual is officially representing the community in public spaces. Examples of representing our community include using an official e-mail address, posting via an official social media account, or acting as an appointed representative at an online or offline event.
            h2.select-none.font-poppins.text-3xl.font-bold.text-neutral-900 Enforcement
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900
              | Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported to the community leaders responsible for enforcement at support@thefemdevs.com. All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly and fairly.
              br
              br
              | All community leaders are obligated to respect the privacy and security of the reporter of any incident.
            h2.select-none.font-poppins.text-3xl.font-bold.text-neutral-900 Enforcement Guidelines
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900 Community leaders will follow these Community Impact Guidelines in determining the consequences for any action they deem in violation of this Code of Conduct:
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-2xl.font-bold.text-neutral-900 1. Correction
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900
              .font-semibold.underline Community Impact: 
              | Use of inappropriate language or other behavior deemed unprofessional or unwelcome in the community.
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900 
              .font-semibold.underline Consequence: 
              | A private, written warning from community leaders, providing clarity around the nature of the violation and an explanation of why the behavior was inappropriate. A public apology may be requested.
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-2xl.font-medium.text-neutral-900 2. Warning
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900 
              .font-semibold.underline Community Impact:
              | A violation through a single incident or series of actions.
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900
              .font-semibold.underline Consequence:
              | A warning with consequences for continued behavior. No interaction with the people involved, including unsolicited interaction with those enforcing the Code of Conduct, for a specified period of time. This includes avoiding interactions in community spaces as well as external channels like social media. Violating these terms may lead to a temporary or permanent ban.
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-2xl.font-medium.text-neutral-900 3. Temporary Ban
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900
              .font-semibold.underline Community Impact: 
              | A serious violation of community standards, including sustained inappropriate behavior.
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900 
              .font-semibold.underline Consequence: 
              | A temporary ban from any sort of interaction or public communication with the community for a specified period of time. No public or private interaction with the people involved, including unsolicited interaction with those enforcing the Code of Conduct, is allowed during this period. Violating these terms may lead to a permanent ban.
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-2xl.font-medium.text-neutral-900 4. Permanent Ban
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900 
              .font-semibold.underline Community Impact: 
              | Demonstrating a pattern of violation of community standards, including sustained inappropriate behavior, harassment of an individual, or aggression toward or disparagement of classes of individuals.
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900 
              .font-semibold.underline Consequence: 
              | A permanent ban from any sort of public interaction within the community.
            h2.select-none.font-poppins.text-3xl.font-bold.text-neutral-900 Attribution
            h3.select-none.font-poppins.text-xl.text-neutral-900
